Reasoning: The paper discusses the selection and coding of benchmarks for the EURETILE project, which focuses on the software and hardware architecture of future many-tile distributed fault-tolerant systems for dynamic workloads with heavy numerical processing requirements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Architecture (cs.AR), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
